inn1.comm: well bowled off cutter, Martyn plays down the wrong line and is trapped plumb in front, Pollock too joins the party
drifting down the leg side, played down to fine leg for an easy single
pitched up in the slot outside the off stump and Gilchrist drills it through the narrow gap between the cover fielders
short of a good length delivery, driven off the back-foot, de Villiers at covers moves across quickly to his left, slides across and saves a certain boundary
driven to covers
short and wide outside the off stump, Gilchrist makes room and cuts it away behind point
driven wide of the cover fielder

good length delivery outside the off stump, Clarke gets forward and drives it straight down the ground to the long-off fence, didn't try to hit it too hard, just got behind the line and punched it wide of the fielder, good shot!
forced away towards point
beaten outside the off stump
defended to point
defended
played away on the leg side
short delivery outside the off stump, Gilchrist goes after it and gets beaten - beaten by the extra bounce there

width offered outside the off stump and Gilchrist hammer it towards point, Pietersen there fails to hold on to a fairly easy chance - that ball was travelling but it went more-or-less straight to Pietersen
turned away to fine leg
driven straight to the fielder at mid-off

short of a good length delivery, Gilchrist goes for his favourite pull but the ball moves in a touch and that cramps him but it's too late to adjust and the top edge balloons up towards mid-on, Nel nicely settles under it
forced away behind point
defended outside the off stump
on the front-foot, defended
defended towards point
left alone outside the off stump
turned away off the pads to deep fine leg for one
short of a length, lets it through to the wicketkeeper
good length delivery outside off, defebnded off the frontfoot to the man at cover
good length delivery outside off, Clarke comes forward and defends to the man at cover
short of a length this time, Clarke goes onto his backfoot, presents the full face of the bat and defends to the offside
short of a length again, defended off the backfoot to the offside
full delivery on the middle and leg, its driven down the ground to mid-on
full delivery outside off, Clarke comes forward and plays it away to the man at cover-point
driven to cover point
good length delivery outside off, left through to the wicketkeeper
good length delivery, shaping away just a bit, left through to the wicketkeeper
full delivery outside off, shaping away again, left alone
good length delivery outside off and holding its line, left through to the wicketkeeper again - this is good bowling from Polock, testing the batsmen here
good length delivery again, Hussey drops it on the offside and takes off for a quick single
outside off and angling across, left alone
good length delivery outside off and angling across, Hussey fishes for it outside off and is beaten by the angle
short of a length outside offm, Hussey gets to the line of the ball and shoulders arms
good length delivery outside off and anglign across the left hander, left through to the wicketkeeper
good length delivery again, and its left through to the wicketkeeper again
good length delivery on the stumps, Hussey comes forward and plays it with soft hands, that delivery was just a shade slower, no chance of a run though
good length delivery in line with the stumps, its driven straight back down the ground, knocks the stump at the non-strikers end out of the groudn
short of a length outside off, its driven away backward of point off the backfoot for a single
short of a length outside off, plays it away backward of point for a single
driven straight down the ground for a boundary
starts off with a good length ball, its driven away to cover point for a single

shot! short of a length outside off, and it was asking to be hit, Clarjke does just that - he cuts it away in the air, past a diving fielder at cover - the ball races away to the cover fence for a boundary
shot!! two boundaries in a row, good lenght ball, Clarke drives it handsomely down the ground - the ball races away to the long-off boundary
good length delivery, Clarke shoulders arms and lets it through to the wicketkeeper
starts off with a good length ball, its defended to the offside
short of a length outside off, Hussey gets behind the line of the ball and lets it through to the wicketkeeper
short of a length deliveryu again, Hussey stands tall, opens the face of the bat and runs it down in between gully and slip, the ball races away to the thirdman boundary
short of a length outside off, its let through to the wicketkeeper

outside off, Clarke shoulders arms and thinks of letting it through to the wicketkeeper, the ball comes in just a bit and takes the edge of the bat and runs down to thirdman, enough time for a single there
short of a length outside off, its left through to the wicketkeeper
Nel drifts on the pads this time and Hussey works it away backward of square, take two quick runs before the fielder fom fine leg can come and tidy up the ball
short of a length outside off, Hussey stands on the backfoot and plays with soft hands, takes a quick single before Nel can field on his follow-through
good length ball, driven straight back down the ground with a straight bat, its fantastically fielded by Nel on his follow through
drifts on middle and leg this time, Clarke works it away off his pads, straight to the man at mid-wicket
good length delivery outside off, Hussey plays it away on the off-side

good running there! good length delivery on the stumps, Hussey plays it away to the offside with soft hands and takes off for a quick single, they chance Gibbs' arm, but make it comfortably in the end
good length ball, drifts on the pads this time, its worked away behind square for a single
pitched up outside the off stump, driven down to mid-off
pitched up outside the off stump, driven down to mid-off
defended straight back down the track, Nel picks it up and his throw back to the keeper hits Clarke
driven through midwicket
on the pads, defended on the back-foot and the ball rolls away on the leg side
pitched up on the pads, flicked away to fine leg for a single
good length delivery, hint of inswing, defended down on the leg side
driven into the gap between mid-off and cover
short of a good length delivery outside the off stump, defended standing tall on the back-foot
left alone outside the off stump
coming in with the angle, left through to the keeper
short of a good length delivery, Hussey cuts off the back-foot and the ball flies off the edge, Pollock at third man had no chance of cutting it off
left alone outside the off stump
short and angling in, Hussey gets right behind the line and defends it down watchfully
another quick delivery outside the off stump, this time Hussey leaves it through to the keeper
leg-cutter, this one died on its way to the keeper, Hussey was not interested
fraction short, bit of width offered outside the off stump and Clarke cuts it past the fielder at gully, easy single
pitched up in the slot outside the off stump, Hussey drive hard and the ball goes straight to the fielder at extra cover
short of a good length delivery on the legs, Hussey moves forward and across and turns it away on the leg side for a single, nicely played
played into the gap between mid-on and midwicket, easy single added to the total
shot! short rising delivery, pitched in line and angling across, Hussey stands up tall on the back-foot, gets right on top of the bounce and pulls it away to the midwicket fence
defended down towards mid-off
driven to mid-off
good length delivery, hint of swing, Clarke gets a good stride forward, covers his stumps and leaves it through to the keeper
turned away behind square for an easy single
bowled from round the stumps, close to the off stump line and Hussey carefully blocks it down on the off side
short of a good length delivery outside the off stump, no shot offered
defended to point
good length delivery outside the off stump, forced away off the front-foot and the ball goes straight to the fielder at cover
off-cutter outside the off stump, bit too wide to interest the batsman
slightly short, pulled away well in front of point, not a well timed shot and the fielder catches up
down the leg side, Clarke fails to make contact
glided down to third man
driven down to long-off
forced away straight to Pietersen at point
glided past the fielder at second slip, easy single
good length delivery outside the off stump, hint of away swing, no shot offered
turned away behind point for an easy single
defended down on the track, half hearted appeal for lbw turned down
straight delivery, turned away behind square for an easy single
starts off with a wide delivery outside the off stump, Hussey watchfully leaves it through to the keeper
tossed up outside the off stump, driven down to long-on for an easy single
Clarke straight away comes down the track, takes it on the full and drives it down to long-off for a single
defended outside the off stump, ball rolls back to the bowler
fulltoss, worked away to deep square leg  for a single
turned away straight to the fielder at short fine leg, Pietersen starts off with a decent over
width offered outside the off stump, cut away well in front of point for a single
turn and bounce but down the leg side and that's right called a wide
Smith drags it down short and Clarke pulls it away to fine leg, Pollock is the fielder in the deep
forced away wide of the point fielder
nicely driven down to long-on for an easy single
tossed up outside the off stump, bowled from round the stumps, Hussey leans well forward and paddles it down to fine leg
tossed up outside the off stump, defended
turned away towards midwicket, no room for a single there
comes down the track, takes it on the full and flays it away to the cover fence, sweeper had no chance of cutting it off
forced away towards midwicket
turned away wide of the midwicket fielder
turned away on the leg side
fraction short outside the off stump and Hussey goes for the pull but gets nowhere with the shot
driven down to long-off for a single
steps forward, gets to the pitch of the delivery and drives hard but fails to get it past the fielder at cover
turned away to the fine leg region for an easy singe and that brings up the Australian 100
cut away off the back-foot to deep cover
quicker delivery, on the pads and Clarke turns it away well wide of the fielder deep midwicket
drifts on the pads this time, its worked away to the midwicket region for a single
tossed up delivery, Clarke comes down the track, but when he realises theres not enough room to free his arms, he defneds
short delivery, Clarke goes onto the backfoot and pulls it away, there's a man patrolling the squareleg fence, so its just a single
good improvisation on that occasion, Hussey plays the reverse sweep, the ball is played fine down o the thirdman region, its a brilliant effort by Smith to pull it back
short delivery from Peterson, its cut away off the backfoot for a single
full toss, its driven down the ground to longon for a single, that single wil take Clarke to his fifty
short delivery from Smith from round the stumps, Hussey goes onto the backfoot and pulls it away to the vacant spaces in the midwicket region
tossed up delivery, its driven down to longoff for a single
worked away off the pads to the squareleg for a single

shot!! thats a fantastic way to bring up your fifty! tossed up delivery outside off, Hussey pulls it away high and wide over the fence at mid-wicket, there was a man patrolling the fence there, but he had absolutely no chance
played back to Smith
driven straight to the man at cover
worked away off the pads, backward of square for a single
opens the face of the bat  to a tossed up delivery and runs it down backward of point for a single
played away on the off-side
worked away off the pads to backward of square for a single, that single brings up the 100 partnership between the two
flicked away to mid-wicket, Peterseon runs across from his followthrough and fields it
good length delivery outside off, Clarke comes forward and defends, tries to work it away on the onside, but doesnt find the gap

Pollock strikes!! slower delivery from Pollock, just a bit on offer, Clarke falls prey to it, drives in the air, but cant find the gap, drives to the left of AB De Villiers who's fielding at cover, he dives to his left and pulls off a fantastic catch!
outside off, Watson has a good look at it and lets it through to the wicketkeeper
good length ball outside off, driven away to the man at cover
good length delivery outside off, just a bit of bounce on that occasion, Watson comes forward to defend, the ball hits the shoulder of the bat and runs away on the offside
good length delivery to wind up the over, Watson comes forward and defends
tossed up delivery on off and middle, Hussey drives it down the ground to long-on
tossed up delivery, Watson drives it straight into the man fielding at short mid-off
good length ball, tossed up kjust a bit, tries to drive it down to mid-off, Peterson runs across from his follow-through and cuts it off
full toss, driven away for a single
full toss, bowls from over the wickets now, its driven down the ground to long-off for a single
yet another single to complete the over, just a little short in length and just a bit of width too, Watson cuts it away to deep point for a single
short of a length outside off, Watson stands tall and punches it away through the gap between cover and mid-off for a single
good length delivery in line with the stumps, its driven away to mid-off, no chance of a run there
worked away off the pads to deep backward squareleg, quick running by the Aussie batsmen, and a throw to the wrong end means the Aussies pinch two runs easily

gone!! that was a rank bad shot. Pollock bowls one just a little short, and a little too straight, Hussey pulls it away off the backfoot, cant keep it down, and finds Boeta Dippenaar at the midwicket fence - that's two wickets in two overs for Pollock - justifies Graeme Smith's move of bringing him on
defended outside the off stump
probin delivery outside the off stump and Hogg watchfully leaves it through to the keeper
fuller and quicker, defended stretching well forward
driven straight back down the track to the mid-on region, diving stop there from Hall saves runs
punched away wide of the bowler
forced away wide of the gully fielder, quick single taken
driven to mid-off for a single
good length delivery outside the off stump, Watson leaves it through to the keeper
another tight delivery, close to the off stump line and Watson defends it on the front-foot
played down to mid-off
pitched up on the pads, flicked away straight to the fielder at fine leg
good length delivery on the middle and off stump line, Hogg gets behind the line and drives it away towards cover, fielder moves in quickly and negates the chance of a single
driven away nicely opening the face of the bat, gets it wide of the fielder at third man
On the pads, turned away on the leg side
low fulltoss outside the off stump but Lee misses out, only manages it punch it down to long-on for a single
forced away towards cover point, well judges quick single taken
bouncer, this one nipped back in, Lee ducks under it - well played in the end.
another short delivery, Lee fends it away on the off side, slight mix-up going for the single but in the end they make it across safely
driven straight down the ground to long-on, was looking for two but the fielder moves across quickly and cuts it off
short delivery down the leg side, ball clips the thigh pad and rolls away behind the stumps on the leg side, Bouncer moves across and keeps it down to just one
another leg-bye, Hall once again drifting down the leg side, Lee fails to make contact and the ball rolls away off the pad
short ball down the leg side, wrong line, hooked away straight to the fielder at fine leg, just a single
full and on middle and leg, driven down to long-on for a brace, excellent running between the wickets, Pollock was the fielder in the deep
short rising delivery, angling in from outside the off stump, Lee stands tall on the back-foot and fends it away on the leg side, easy single
good length delivery, punched back to the bowler - end of a good over
fuller length delivery on the middle and leg stump line, Lee beautifully flicks it away well wide of midwicket, fielder in the deep moves across quickly and keeps it down to two
played away well in front of point
forced away towards cover, direct hit at the bowler's end but Lee was never in trouble
slightly short and close to the off stump line, Lee cuts hard but fails to make contact
good length delivery outside the off stump, driven down to long-off, de Villiers is the fielder in the deep
bouncer on the stumps, too high and that's called a wide
fulltoss, Lee gets hit on the pad and the ball rolls away towards point, throw at the striker's end is off target - overthrow and they finally cross over
flicked away past the diving square leg fielder
pitched up outside the off stump and Lee hammers it towards cover, another brilliant stop by de Villiers saves runs
well directed short delivery, Lee can only fend it away off the back-foot, ball rolls away towards point - well bowled
half volley on the stumps and Lee dills it straight back past the bowler to long-off, good sliding effort in the deep save runs
full and angling in, driven away to deep midwicket, came off the inner half of the bat
smashed down the track to long-off, Pollock fails to stop it cleanly but no damage is done, single to end the over
pitched up and angling in and Lee thulps it straight back down the track, almost took out the non-striker
massive six! right in the slot and that's dispatched over the long-on fence, good clean hit!
short delivery down the leg side, Nel under pressure here
good length delivery outside the off stump, Lee winds up and swings across but fails to make contact, few words of wisdom exchanged
another short delivery down the leg side and the umpire is not happy with the width
fulltoss down the leg side, Nel is really struggling here - Bouncer dives across and saves a certain four
bang! and the ball sails over the midwicket fence - stand and deliver, Lee at his best and this is turning out to be a massive over for Australia
another fuller length delivery and this time Lee hammers it straight back down the track to the long-off region, fantastic diving effort by de Villiers cuts off the boundary
played away on the leg side, easy single to end the over
short ball, awkward looking pull and the ball rolls away behind square
Hall strikes back! full and on the stump, Watson misses and Hall hits
driven back, Hall moves across on his follow through and cuts off the single
good length delivery outside the off stump, driven just wide of the fielder at mid-off and they steal a single

short of a good length delivery, Lee pulls and for once fails to time it properly, ball clips the top edge and lobs up on the leg side but luckily for Lee the ball falls well wide of the fielder at midwicket
excellent yorker to end the voer, Bracken jabs it towards gully and they go for the single
good length delivery on the middle and off stump line, Bracken gets a good stride forward and lofts it over the wide long-on fence, another massive six
lofted away to deep midwicket, Gibbs hurtles across from long-on and cuts off the boundary
Bracken continues to impress! fulltoss on the pads, probably the yorker gone wrong and that's pounded over the midwicket fence, Ntini being taken apart here
swing and a miss and they run, Bouncer fails to hits the stumps and Lee makes it across safely

RUN OUT! wide delivery outside the off stump and the ball goes through to the keeper, Bracken takes off for the run but this time Lee stands his ground, with both the batsmen at the same end the ball is throw to Ntini, who strolls across and clips the bails at the bowler's end
beaten outside the off stump
yorker, Lee digs it out to long-off for a brace and Australia end up with 229 on the board

inn2.comm: left alone outside the off stump
on middle and leg and that's nicely clipped away to the midwicket fence
turned away on the leg side, quick single taken and that brings Dippenaar to the fore
short of a good length delivery, defended on the front-foot
good length delivery outside the off stump, hint of swing, Dippenaar goes for the drive and gets beaten

take that! good length delivery outside the off stump, Dippenaar stands his ground and drills it past the point fielder - ball rocketed away off the middle of the blade, what a shot to get off the mark!&
good length delivery, swinging away, Smith leaves it through to the keeper
short of a good length delivery, this one went straight-on, no shot offered
short of a good length, swinging away from the left-hander, Smith moves back and across and forces it away towards cover
defended outside the off stump
width offered outside the off stump, cut away behind point
another wide delivery outside the off stump, Smith cuts but fails to get it past the point fielder
defended on the front-foot
swing and a miss outside the off stump
short rising delivery outside the off stump, bit of a surprise delivery, Dippenaar stands tall on the back-foot and steers it down to third man for a single
short delivery on the middle and leg stump line, Smith hops on the back-foot, gets on top of the bounce and gently plays it down on the leg side
played down to fine leg
shot! good length delivery outside the off stump and Dippenaar plays a classic cover drive, ball races away through the narrow gap between mid-off and cover, no stopping that
defended on the leg side
inside edge and the ball rolls away towards square leg
good length delivery outside the off stump, defended
short of a good length and swinging away, bit too wide and Smith watchfully leaves it through to the keeper
way outside the off stump
played down behind the stumps
defended on the front-foot
defended

short ball, pitched in line and angling across, Smith sways back and pulls it away well wide of the fielder at square, was in the air for sometime but went well wide of the fielder, excellent placement
short and wide outside the off stump, cut away to third man for an easy single
left alone outside the off stump
short delivery down the leg side, off the glove and the ball rolls away behind square
short rising delivery on the middle and off stump line, defended with a straight bat and the ball rolls back to the bowler
line and length delivery, driven straight back to the bowler
good length delivery, hint of swing, steered down to third man
pitched up outside the off stump, driven straight to the fielder at point
good length delivery on the middle and off stump line, defended on the front-foot
forced away towards cover

good length delivery on the middle and off stump line, Dippenaar defends on the back-foot with a straight bat, ball keeps low, clips the toe end of the bat and crashes into the off stump - Bracken with the breakthrough!
defended down to mid-off
short and wide outside the off stump, Smith climbs on top of it and whips it away to the cover fence, shot of a man in-form!
defended on the front-foot
good length delivery, this one swung back in, Smith plays down the wrong line and gets hit on the pad, confident appeal turned down - close call
Clarke! fuller on the pads and that's flicked straight to Clarke at midwicket, that ball was travelling, Clarke takes it cleanly and hits the stumps at the bowler's end,  Gibbs is caught napping!
edged past the slip cordon
turned away to fine leg
forced away towards mid-on
defended
turned away to deep square leg, just makes it back for the third
steered down to short third man
left alone outside the off stump
defended down on the off side, quick single taken
defended outside the off stump
pitched up outside the off stump, de Villiers drive opening the face of the bat and the ball races away to the backward point fence, excellent timing and placement
driven away on the off side, no room for a single there
forced away towards point
short and wide outside the off stump, that's a bad delivery and de Villiers drills it away through cover point
full delivery outside off, Smith drives it nice and handsome through extra cover, Watson manages to pull it back into the field of play just in time
good length delivery, de Villiers defends it with a straight bat, the ball runs away to the man at gully
short delivery, de Villers plays an ambitious pull, the ball takes the top edge and balloons up in the air, Watson moves around from mid-on, but cant hang on to the ball, drops a tough one
good length ball, Smith aiming for the cover drive, the ball comes in just a bit, takes the inside edge of the bat and rolls away behind the stumps
driven away to mid-off
driven to mid-on
starts off with a good length ball, nicely driven away to cover

short of a good length outside off, Smith goes onto his backfoot and aims to cut it away through point, goes through with the shot, but the ball takes the inside half of the bat and rolls away to the man at cover
short of a good length, just a bit of width on offer, cut away past point for a brace, thats good running by the South African duo
good length delivery this time, just a little too straight, played away off the pads to Katich at squareleg
length delivery yet again, moving into Smith just a bit, worked off the pads to the squareleg region, pick up a single before Katich can move around and field it
length delivery on the pads, de Villiers chances his arms at the pull shot, doesnt middle it as well as he would have liked, the ball comes off the glove and rolls away to Gilchrist behind the stumps
defended off the frontfoot
short and wide, Smith cuts it away in between point and cover and takes two runs before the ball is returned to Gilchrist
short delivery on the stumps, Smith goes onto the backfoot and pulls it away, doesnt get hold of it as well as he would have liked, the ball lands in no man's land
full delivery outside off, handsomely driven in the gap between cover and mid-off, there was no chance of stopping that one
Lewis strays on the pads this time, its worked away to the onside, but straight to the man at square-leg
good length delivery, its played away to point, de Villiers opens the face of the bat and makes contact pretty late
shot!! that ball was full and asking to be hit, de Villiers leans into the shot, and sends the ball racing between the man at cover and mid-off

shot!! just a xerox copy of the previous shot.nothing wrong with that delivery, but de Villiers is seeing the ball so well that he punches it in between the gap between cover and mid-off, the ball races away to the extra-cover fence - neither the mid-off or the cover fielder had any chance of stopping that
shot!! what a way to round off the over, that was a short delivery, and de Villiers, seeing the ball as big as a foot ball, rocks back and pulls it away high and wide over the fence at squareleg
good length ball, Smith stays on the backfoot and cuts it away late, the ball races down to deep thirdman and the south AFricans pick up an easy single
wayward delivery from Lewis, pressure starting to show on the Aussies now, Lewis loses his idrection, strays down the legside, rightly called wide by Umpire Lloyds
good length delivery, driven away to the cover fence in style
swept away to deep square leg
defended outside the off stump
short rising delivery, pitched close to the off stump line and angling across, Smith sways away late
worked away through square leg
short of a good length delivery, punched off the back-foot to the cover region
cut down to third man for a single
good delivery on the stumps, opens up de Villiers and produces the edge, ball races away to the third man fence
steered down to third man

short and wide outside the off stump, de Villiers cuts off the back-foot and ends up with a faint edge, Boucher holds on well to a fairly hard chance - de Villiers was looking good and that's a big wicket
defended down on the leg side
turned away on the leg side, midwicket moves across and cuts off the single
defended outside the off stump
driven back past the bowler, diving stop at mid-on saves runs
short ball, pulled away to deep backward square leg - rolled the wrists over nicely to keep it down
full and drifting down the leg side, Smith drives but makes no contact, Lee goes up for the catch but the umpire is not interested
short of a good length delivery on the middle and off stump line, defended
fuller length delivery on the middle and leg stump line, Smith looking to flick it away through midwicket is bit early into the shot, ball hits the pad and rolls away on the leg side
down the leg side
cut away straight to the fielder placed right in front of point
turned away well in front of square leg, they run hard looking for the second but the fielder moves across quickly and cuts it off
juicy full outside the off stump and that's punched past the midwicket fielder with brute force - no stopping that
driven straight to the fielder at cover
quicker delivery, Smith goes back, gets right behind the line and defends it down
leading edge and the ball rolls back to the bowler, Smith was looking to drive through cover
fulltoss outside the off stump, driven wide of the cover fielder
short delivery on the middle and off stump line, Smith goes for the pull and is bit early into the shot, ball clips the bottom edge and goes through between the keeper and the slip - lucky runs
turned away in the air to the midwicket region, not a well timed shot and the ball popped up off the edge, fell well short of the fielder though
driven straight to the fielder at midwicket
driven straight to the fielder at mid-off
good length delivery outside the off stump, punched straight to the fielder at mid-off
pitched up outside the off stump, Boucher drives well but fails to beat the fielder at cover
slower delivery outside the off stump, forced away behind point, Lee moves across and cuts off the single
slightly short and close to the off stump line, Smith sways back and cuts it away well wide of the fielder at backward point
good length delivery outside the off stump, hint of movement, Smith fails to time his shot and the ball rolls away off the inner half of the bat, cover fielder moves in and picks it up
drifting down the leg side, Smith moves across a bit and tucks it away well wide of the fielder at short fine leg, easy single added to the total
pitched up on the pads, turned away through square leg for an easy single, good cricket this from Boucher
inside edge and the ball rolls away on the leg side
good length delivery outside the off stump, forced away towards cover
short of a good length delivery, close to the off stump line, Boucher gets a good stride forward and defends it down on the off side
drifting down the leg side and Boucher works it away on the leg side for an easy single
fuller length delivery outside the off stump, driven down to mid-off and they sprint across for a single, not a well timed shot and the ball came off the inner half of the bat
called for overstepping, short of a good length delivery outside the off stump and Boucher leaves it through to the keeper
good length delivery outside the off stump, driven off the front-foot and the ball goes straight to the cover fielder, who is at the edge of the circle

turned away behind square leg where Katich mis-fields, big mix-up going for the second, captain and the keeper end up on the same side of the wicket - throws comes in to the bowler's end and Lee flicks the bails
driven down to mid-off
steered down to third man, easy single and Kemp is off the mark
flicked away to deep square leg
defended towards covewr
beaten by a beauty
beaten outside the off stump
defended down on the leg side
turned away wide of the fielder at midwicket
beaten outside the off stump
driven down to log-on
short ball, pulled away to deep midwicket
short of a good length delivery outside the off stump, no shot offered
full delivery on middle and leg, Smith works it away to mid-wicket, good diving stop by Martyn who flights himself to his left and saves a run
defended to the offside off the frontfoot
full delivery outside off, nicely driven into the gap between cover and mid-off, take an easy single

leg cutter outside off, Smith stays on the backfoot, opens the face of the bat and late cuts it, with the thirdman fielder inside the circle, it was always going to be a boundary once it was played in the gap
driven down to long-on for a single
good length ball to the right hander, its defended back to the bowler
full delivery on the legs, worked away for a brace
good length ball, plays it away to point
forced away towards point
hit on the pad, missing leg and the appeal is turned down
pushed away towards cover, quick single taken
short of a good length delivery outside the off stump, no shot offered
tossed up outside the off stump, defended on the front-foot
flighted delivery outside the off stump, Smith comes down the track and plays it straight to the fielder at midwicket
